# Python Function And Call Style

When a function has one obvious primary argument plus secondary configuration
arguments, make the secondary arguments keyword-only with `*`.

```python
def profile_model(
    model_path: str,
    *,
    device: str,
    batch_size: int,
) -> ProfileResult:
    ...
```

Prefer calling functions with explicit keyword arguments, especially when
passing through variables with matching names.

```python
profile_model(
    model_path=model_path,
    device=device,
    batch_size=batch_size,
)
```

Do not force this pattern when positional arguments are clearer for a small,
well-known API or when matching an established third-party interface.
